<div type="definition">
<p>COMBINE so as to CAUSE TO BECOME ONE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for the unification of what is disunited is yī 一 (ant. fēn 分 "divide").</p>
<p>2. Kuāng 匡 (ant. sàn 散 "spread and disunite") is an elevated expression referring to political unification.</p>
<p>3. Tǒng 統 (ant. zhī 支 "divide into smaller units") focusses on the inner coherence of what is united.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>統一 is the currrent modern word for uniting.</p>
<p>同一 is sometimes used to refer to identification.</p>
